page.title: 1710 YEARS OF CHANGE REDDITCH
page.content: We found a map of{Headless Cross}of 10 years ago,and the first thing that was immediately apparent,were the dramatic changes that had taken place. Because of the {New Town}expansion of{ {Redditch,}this area like most others around here have been developed.From the map most of the open farmland and grassland has been replaced with residential areas.Although part of the area has been turned into parkland. The network of roads and highways built recently to link the new housing estates looks very different on the map than the old streets. The eastern part of our section has been residential for a long time,and the difference between the old and new areas makes for a very interesting study.
